<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7495</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                                Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-09">February 9, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Hamilton</hi>: It occurs to me that it might be
                            good strategy and of advantage all around were this Department to
                            formulate immediately some proposal for the making available to China as
                            promptly as possible some part or parts of the $500,000,000 that became
                            available for financial aid to China last week.</p>
                        <p>Would you be so good as to take general charge of this question,
                            consulting and collaborating with personnel of other offices who are or
                            should be concerned.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps">ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>